    MgCoordinateSystemMeasure

    public class MgMeasure
extends MgGuardDisposable
    MgMeasure is an abstract class that can be implemented to provide non-linear measurement for geometry operations.

      • getAzimuth

        public double getAzimuth(MgCoordinate coord1,
                         MgCoordinate coord2)
        (NOTE: This API is not officially supported and may be subject to removal in a future release without warning. Use with caution.) Gets the angle with respect to the north of a vector formed by two coordinates.
        Parameters:
        coord1 - An MgCoordinate that specifies the first coordinate.
        coord2 - An MgCoordinate that specifies the second coordinate.
        Returns:

      • getCoordinate

        public MgCoordinate getCoordinate(MgCoordinate coord,
                                  double azimuth,
                                  double distance)
        (NOTE: This API is not officially supported and may be subject to removal in a future release without warning. Use with caution.) Computes a coordinate a given distance along a vector that is defined by a starting coordinate and an azimuth (Angle with respect to the North).
        Parameters:
        coord - An MgCoordinate that represents the start of the vector.
        azimuth - An azimuth (Angle with respect to the North) that defines the direction of the vector.
        distance - The distance along the vector of the desired coordinate in Meters.
        Returns:
        An MgCoordinate that lies the given distance along the vector.
